What you need to know:

A multi-agency team that has been studying the effects of the moratorium is expected to release its report this month.The price of a 90kg bag has risen from Sh500 to Sh3,000. The 2kg tin price has doubled from Sh50 to Sh100.People who lost their jobs because of the Covid-19 economic shut down have also turned to charcoal for a living.Up to 82 per cent of urban and 34 per cent of rural households use charcoal for cooking. The Sh42 billion a year sector supports more than a million people.